        "ingredients": ["1 boneless rib eye steak, 1 1/2-inch thick", "Canola oil, to coat", "Kosher salt", "Ground black pepper"],
        "steps": [
          "Place a 10- to 12-inch cast iron skillet in the oven and heat the oven to 500F.",
          "Bring the steak(s) to room temperature.",
          "When the oven reaches temperature, remove the pan and set it over high heat on the range.",
          "Coat the steak lightly with oil and season both sides with a generous pinch of salt.",
          "Grind on black pepper to taste.",
          "Immediately place the steak in the middle of the hot, dry pan. Cook 30 seconds without moving.",
          "Turn with tongs and cook another 30 seconds, then put the pan straight into the oven for 2 minutes.",
          "Flip the steak and cook another 2 minutes (for medium rare; add a minute per side for medium).",
          "Remove the steak, cover loosely with foil, and rest 2 minutes.",
          "Serve whole or slice thin and fan onto the plate."
